Syntactical illustratione are furnished by the usage of anastrophe of conjunctione and prep- ositions, et before negatives, et in asyndetic collocations, change and repetition of prepositions, the use of particles and the like.

The cumulative weight of this evidence in proof of a genetic development in Tacitean style is considerable, but it is perhaps most conspicuous in the decreasing frequency of synonymous col- locations, discussed above, inasmuch as the fondness for such com- binations 18 equally characteristic of many other writers, Quintilian alone forming 0 rather remarkable exception, when we consider the length of the Institutio.
